{"id": "glr1665702698008", "title": "Addressing Environment Variables with $setting", "breadcrumbs": ["Uniface Reference", "ProcScript Reference", "ProcScript: Functions", "$setting", "Addressing Environment Variables with $setting"], "url": "https://docs.rocketsoftware.com/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/glr1665702698008.html", "html": "<html><body><header class=\"zDocsTopicPageHead\"><h1 class=\"css-g931ng\">Addressing Environment Variables with $setting</h1><div class=\"zDocsTopicActions\" role=\"list\"><div class=\"zDocsBundlePagination\" data-testid=\"next-prev-container\" role=\"listitem\"><div class=\"zDocsPrevTopicButton zDocsPrevTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Previous:  Addressing Initialization and Assignment Settings with $setting  \" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Previous:  Addressing Initialization and Assignment Settings with $setting  \" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bno1665702697862.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-prev\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-prev\"></use></svg></a></span></div><div class=\"zDocsNextTopicButton zDocsNextTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Next:  Addressing Runtime Settings with $setting   \" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Next:  Addressing Runtime Settings with $setting   \" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hkb1665702697936.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></a></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsMyDocsMenu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Add to My Topics\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Add to My Topics\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" id=\"addToMyDocsDropdownTrigger\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg>Add to My Topics</span><div aria-labelledby=\"pdfDropdown\" class=\"dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right\"><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/glr1665702698008.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub\">Add selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/glr1665702698008.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub_head\">Add Topic &amp; Subtopics with topic head</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/glr1665702698008.html?finish_action=mydocs_pub\">Add entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsWatchButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Watch\" class=\"d-lg-flex d-none zDocsSubscribeButton\" data-tooltip-content=\"Watch\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsSubscribeButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye zDocsSubscribeButton\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsSubscribeButton\">Watch</span></span></div><div class=\"zDocsExportPdfMenu zDocsExportMenu\" data-testid=\"export-pdf-menu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Download PDF\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Download PDF\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#ZdExportPDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527907\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527907\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 11, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104glr1665702698008.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/glr1665702698008.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/glr1665702698008.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"glr1665702698008\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                           \n Addressing Environment Variables with $setting \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$setting</span> to retrieve and set environment variables or their platform-specific equivalents\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"glr1665702698008__p_d89108e1_d89109e1_d89110e1\">\n<span class=\"ph\">—data areas and environment variables on iSeries\n </span>\n                             . On Windows and Unix, it is only possible to address environment variables for the current process.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"glr1665702698008__topic_d89111e1_d89112e1_d89113e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"glr1665702698008__p_d89114e1_d89115e1_d89116e1\">Retrieve environment variables:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"glr1665702698008__p_d89117e1_d89118e1_d89119e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ReturnedValue</var> = <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$setting</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Source</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">RetrieveProfile</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code>\n<span class=\"keyword parmname\">ENVVARS</span> | <span class=\"keyword parmname\">ENVDATA</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code>\n                           )</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section pre\" id=\"glr1665702698008__section_w505ab1b5b5_w506ab1b5_w507ab1\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">vEnvVariables = $setting (\"\", \"u<span class=\"ph gold\">*</span>\", \"ENVVARS\") \nvEnvVar = $setting (\"\", \"SRC\", \"ENVDATA\")</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"glr1665702698008__topic_d89120e1_d89121e1_d89122e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"glr1665702698008__p_d89123e1_d89124e1_d89125e1\">Add or change a setting:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"glr1665702698008__p_d89126e1_d89127e1_d89128e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$setting</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Source</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">EnvironmentVariable</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code>\n<span class=\"keyword parmname\">ENVDATA</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Value</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section pre\" id=\"glr1665702698008__section_w508ab1b5b9_w509ab1b5_w510ab1\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$setting (\"GLOBAL\", \"MYAPP\", \"ENVDATA\") = \"abcd\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"glr1665702698008__section_u44_ryh_1cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d887943e169\">Parameters</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"glr1665702698008__table_d9626e1_d9627e1_d9628e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Parameters</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"glr1665702698008__table_d9626e1_d9627e1_d9628e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Parameter</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"glr1665702698008__table_d9626e1_d9627e1_d9628e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Data Type</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"glr1665702698008__table_d9626e1_d9627e1_d9628e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Description</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"glr1665702698008__table_d9626e1_d9627e1_d9628e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><span class=\"keyword parmname\">ENVDATA</span>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"glr1665702698008__table_d9626e1_d9627e1_d9628e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">String</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"glr1665702698008__table_d9626e1_d9627e1_d9628e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Get or set an environment variable, logical, or data area. Wildcards are\n                           not allowed. The maximum length that can be assigned to an environment\n                           variable is 4096 bytes.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"glr1665702698008__table_d9626e1_d9627e1_d9628e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><span class=\"keyword parmname\">ENVVARS</span>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"glr1665702698008__table_d9626e1_d9627e1_d9628e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">String</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"glr1665702698008__table_d9626e1_d9627e1_d9628e1__entry__3\"> Get a list of environment variables <span class=\"ph\">, data areas (iSeries) </span>.\n                        Wildcards can be used. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"glr1665702698008__table_d9626e1_d9627e1_d9628e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">RetrieveProfile</var>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"glr1665702698008__table_d9626e1_d9627e1_d9628e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">String</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"glr1665702698008__table_d9626e1_d9627e1_d9628e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Profile to retrieve one or more environment variables or their\n                           equivalent. To retrieve multiple sections or settings, you can use the\n                           GOLD * and GOLD ? characters. The profile must match the\n                              <var class=\"keyword varname\">Topic</var>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"glr1665702698008__table_d9626e1_d9627e1_d9628e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">Source</var>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"glr1665702698008__table_d9626e1_d9627e1_d9628e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">String</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"glr1665702698008__table_d9626e1_d9627e1_d9628e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Location of the environment variable or equivalent construct.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"glr1665702698008__ul_sr5_syh_1cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"glr1665702698008__li_d35588e1_d35589e1_d35590e1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Empty string (<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"\"</code>)—default source, which are\n                                 environment variables for the current process.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"glr1665702698008__li_d35591e1_d35592e1_d35593e1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Platform-specific location or keyword on iSeries:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"glr1665702698008__ul_ur5_syh_1cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"glr1665702698008__li_d35594e1_d35595e1_d35596e1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">LibraryName</var>—data area</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"glr1665702698008__li_d35597e1_d35598e1_d35599e1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">*SYS</code>—system-level environment variable</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"glr1665702698008__li_d35600e1_d35601e1_d35602e1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">*SYSVAL</code>—system-level environment\n                                       variable</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"glr1665702698008__li_d35603e1_d35604e1_d35605e1\">\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">*JOB</code>—job-level environment variable; same as\n                                       empty string</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"glr1665702698008__section_p2z_5yh_1cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d887943e365\">Addressing Environment Variables</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"glr1665702698008__p_d89135e1_d89136e1_d89137e1\">To address environment variables (or their equivalent\n            constructs), you need to specify the <var class=\"keyword varname\">Source</var> as an empty string\n               (<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"\"</code>) or a platform-specific source, and the <var class=\"keyword varname\">Topic</var>\n            as <span class=\"keyword parmname\">ENVARS</span> or <span class=\"keyword parmname\">ENVDATA</span>.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"glr1665702698008__note_s3w_wyh_1cc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> On Windows and Unix, you can retrieve both system\n            and local (process-specific) environment variables, but you can only set them for the\n            current process.</div>\n<p class=\"p\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$setting</span><code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code><code class=\"ph codeph\">\"\",</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">EnvironmentVariable</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<span class=\"keyword parmname\">ENVDATA</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$setting</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">\"\",</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">RetrieveProfile</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<span class=\"keyword parmname\">ENVVARS</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"glr1665702698008__p_d89138e1_d89139e1_d89140e1\">On iSeries:</p>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$setting</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">LibraryName</var> | <span class=\"keyword parmname\">*SYS</span> | <span class=\"keyword parmname\">*JOB</span> |\n               <span class=\"keyword parmname\">*SYSVAL</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Setting</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<span class=\"keyword parmname\">ENVDATA</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$setting</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">LibraryName</var> | <span class=\"keyword parmname\">*SYS</span> | <span class=\"keyword parmname\">*JOB</span> |\n               <span class=\"keyword parmname\">*SYSVAL</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">RetrieveProfile</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">,</code>\n<span class=\"keyword parmname\">ENVVARS</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"glr1665702698008__p_d89141e1_d89142e1_d89143e1\">For example:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"glr1665702698008__ul_bjw_wyh_1cc\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"glr1665702698008__li_d35606e1_d35607e1_d35608e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"glr1665702698008__p_d89144e1_d89145e1_d89146e1\">Retrieve a list of variables  within the current process . For example, to get a list of all\n                  environment variables that start with an A: </p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"glr1665702698008__pre_djw_wyh_1cc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">vEnvVars = $setting (\"\", \"A<span class=\"ph gold\">*</span>\", \"ENVVARS\")</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"glr1665702698008__li_d35609e1_d35610e1_d35611e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"glr1665702698008__p_d89147e1_d89148e1_d89149e1\">Retrieve the value of a specific environment\n                  variable:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"glr1665702698008__pre_ejw_wyh_1cc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">vEnvVar = $setting (\"\", \"SRC\", \"ENVDATA\")\nvDataArea = $setting (\"DLM\", \"DLM_ROOT\", \"ENVDATA\")</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"glr1665702698008__li_d35612e1_d35613e1_d35614e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"glr1665702698008__p_d89150e1_d89151e1_d89152e1\">Modify or add a specific environment variable\n                  (or symbol, logical, or data area)</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"glr1665702698008__pre_fjw_wyh_1cc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$setting (\"\", \"SRC\", \"ENVDATA\") = \"c:/u10303\"\n$setting (\"DLM\", \"DLM_ROOT\", \"ENVDATA\") = \"abcd\"</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527907\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527907\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Addressing Environment Variables with $setting Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 11, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Addressing Environment Variables with $setting You can use $setting to retrieve and set environment variables or their platform-specific equivalents —data areas and environment variables on iSeries . On Windows and Unix, it is only possible to address environment variables for the current process. Retrieve environment variables: ReturnedValue = $setting ( Source , RetrieveProfile , \" ENVVARS | ENVDATA \" ) vEnvVariables = $setting (\"\", \"u * \", \"ENVVARS\") vEnvVar = $setting (\"\", \"SRC\", \"ENVDATA\") Copy Add or change a setting: $setting ( Source , EnvironmentVariable , \" ENVDATA \" ) = Value $setting (\"GLOBAL\", \"MYAPP\", \"ENVDATA\") = \"abcd\" Copy Parameters Table 1. Parameters Parameter Data Type Description ENVDATA String Get or set an environment variable, logical, or data area. Wildcards are not allowed. The maximum length that can be assigned to an environment variable is 4096 bytes. ENVVARS String Get a list of environment variables , data areas (iSeries) . Wildcards can be used. RetrieveProfile String Profile to retrieve one or more environment variables or their equivalent. To retrieve multiple sections or settings, you can use the GOLD * and GOLD ? characters. The profile must match the Topic . Source String Location of the environment variable or equivalent construct. Empty string ( \"\" )—default source, which are environment variables for the current process. Platform-specific location or keyword on iSeries: LibraryName —data area *SYS —system-level environment variable *SYSVAL —system-level environment variable *JOB —job-level environment variable; same as empty string Addressing Environment Variables To address environment variables (or their equivalent constructs), you need to specify the Source as an empty string ( \"\" ) or a platform-specific source, and the Topic as ENVARS or ENVDATA . Note: On Windows and Unix, you can retrieve both system and local (process-specific) environment variables, but you can only set them for the current process. $setting ( \"\", EnvironmentVariable , ENVDATA ) $setting ( \"\", RetrieveProfile , ENVVARS ) On iSeries: $setting ( LibraryName | *SYS | *JOB | *SYSVAL , Setting , ENVDATA ) $setting ( LibraryName | *SYS | *JOB | *SYSVAL , RetrieveProfile , ENVVARS ) For example: Retrieve a list of variables within the current process . For example, to get a list of all environment variables that start with an A: vEnvVars = $setting (\"\", \"A * \", \"ENVVARS\") Copy Retrieve the value of a specific environment variable: vEnvVar = $setting (\"\", \"SRC\", \"ENVDATA\") vDataArea = $setting (\"DLM\", \"DLM_ROOT\", \"ENVDATA\") Copy Modify or add a specific environment variable (or symbol, logical, or data area) $setting (\"\", \"SRC\", \"ENVDATA\") = \"c:/u10303\" $setting (\"DLM\", \"DLM_ROOT\", \"ENVDATA\") = \"abcd\" Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}